leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/classroom.png" fade="0.7"]
The professor discusses a complicated lesson.
Students take notes.
Maya stares at the projector.
Trying her best to keep up.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
12:43 A. M.
Maya rubs her eyes.
Her laptop screen glows in the darkness.
An unfinished project remains open.
She sighs heavily.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/campus_hallway.png" fade="0.7"]
Students rush between classes.
Maya and Ethan walk together.
Talking.
Laughing.
For a brief moment, Maya forgets about deadlines.
[signal arg="emotion:nervous"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
The calendar again.
More days crossed out.
The end of the term slowly creeps closer.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
Warm lights glow from inside the house.
The CRUZ'S arrive carrying food containers and drinks.
Jennifer adjusts her blouse.
Ricardo carries a tray.
Maya follows behind them.
join Jennifer (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Jennifer: Make sure to greet everyone properly.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
Maya: Ma, ilang beses na tayong nagdi-dinner together.
Jennifer: And?
Maya: Nothing. Sanay na sila saten, they're literally family, Ma.
join Ricardo (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Ricardo: Your mother just likes reminding people to look their best, anak.
Jennifer shoots him a look of agreement.
They wait for them to enter their house.
Dinner is already underway.
The table is crowded with food.
Conversations overlap.
Laughter occasionally fills the room.
TITA Marie sits near Jennifer while discussing work and family matters.
Ay, before we eat, of course kailangan mag picture-picture muna para sa FB, everyone smile ha.
Everyone turns to Jennifer and poses for a quick photo.
Maya sits beside Ethan.
join Ethan (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Ethan: Glad you decided to take a break from studying and joined tonight.
Maya: As if I had a choice.
Ethan: That's fair, but we all need a break sometimes. You've been working hard.
Maya: How about you? Not busy lately?
Ethan: Oh, I am but I definitely had no choice, Ma told me tita was making a lot of food tonight so I HAD to come with.
The two laugh.
Across the table, Ricardo notices.
Ricardo: You two never run out of things to talk about, no?
Ethan: We've had years of practice, Tito.
All of them share a laugh.
The conversation continues.
People begin finishing their meals.
Then...
TITA Marie smiles toward Ethan.
join Marie (neutral) right [animation="Instant In"]
Marie: So, Ethan.
How's school?
Ethan: It's going okay naman, Ma.
Marie: Just okay?
Ethan: Okay and stressful.
Everyone chuckles.
Ricardo: Ano course mo ulit? Tungkol sa computer diba?
Ethan: Yes po tito, computer science to be exact!
Ricardo: Makes sense, talino mo kasi.
Ethan: Grades are doing alright, praise God.
Everyone laughs.
Jennifer: That's good, alam namin na kaya mo yan, hijo.
Ethan: Hopefully I can keep them there.
Ricardo: Ay sus, Ikaw pa, I'm sure you will.
update Ethan (glad)
Ethan smiles politely.
Jennifer's phone lights up beside her plate, a relative's post about their child's graduation. She glances at it, expression tightening, before pocketing it.
